group: role-ml-engineer
persona: "ML / AI engineer shipping a production LLM / RAG / agent feature."

intent: |
  Move from the messy starting condition to the explicit done state for: Embed RAG into an existing product. Ship a tier-1 RAG feature (retrieval-grounded answers over the product's own corpus) from kickoff to GA: ingestion pipeline live, chunking + embeddings tuned, hybrid retrieval + reranking deployed, eval harness in CI, p95 latency + cost SLOs met, on-call runbook handed to ops.

scope: |
  Ship a tier-1 RAG feature (retrieval-grounded answers over the product's own corpus) from kickoff to GA: ingestion pipeline live, chunking + embeddings tuned, hybrid retrieval + reranking deployed, eval harness in CI, p95 latency + cost SLOs met, on-call runbook handed to ops.

summary: |
  Embed RAG into an existing product. Ship a tier-1 RAG feature (retrieval-grounded answers over the product's own corpus) from kickoff to GA: ingestion pipeline live, chunking + embeddings tuned, hybrid retrieval + reranking deployed, eval harness in CI, p95 latency + cost SLOs met, on-call runbook handed to ops.

non_goals:
  - "Tooling holy wars — picking the stack is a side-effect, not the goal"
  - "Org-design / hiring changes outside the scope of this engagement"
  - "Speculative work without an acceptance criterion to test against"

prerequisites:
  - "Stakeholder + decision-maker named at kickoff"
  - "Access to the systems / dashboards / repos the playbook touches"
  - "Budget signed for the tooling + telemetry this playbook depends on"

success_criteria:
  - "Done-state achieved as described in the scope: Ship a tier-1 RAG feature (retrieval-grounded answers over the product's own corpus) from kickoff to GA: ingestion pipeline live, chunking + embeddings tuned, hybrid retrieval + reranking deployed, eval harness in CI, p95 latency + cost SLOs met, on-call runbook handed to ops."
  - "Decision doc signed: continue / iterate / kill, backed by evidence."
  - "Runbook + acceptance criteria in source control, handed to on-call / next owner."
  - "All must-fix issues from Harden / Pilot closed; nice-to-fix backlog ticketed."

